{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9b5a6693-f6ea-4443-bc06-85608d5e1479","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since this is a general guidance request, here's exactly what to do:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the namespace for your ViewModel and set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — this tells the XAML compiler which type to resolve bindings against.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\n**Compiled bindings are validated at compile time by default** once `x:DataType` is set. A typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure.\n\nTo ensure this is fully enforced, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors (default for new projects) -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Opting out for specific subtrees\n\nIf part of the page binds to a different or dynamic type (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`), you can scope `x:DataType` locally or disable it:\n\n```xml\n<!-- switch type for a nested scope -->\n<CollectionView x:DataType=\"vm:OtherItemViewModel\" ItemsSource=\"{Binding Items}\">\n    ...\n</CollectionView>\n\n<!-- opt out entirely (reverts to reflection-based binding) -->\n<Label x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\" Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProp}\" />\n```\n\n### Summary\n\n| What | How |\n|---|---|\n| Enable compiled bindings | Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element |\n| Catch errors at build time | Misspelled/missing properties become **compiler errors** automatically |\n| Opt out selectively | Use `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"` on specific elements |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"abf5da29-67e7-446e-8d10-2468609880ba","outputTokens":669,"requestId":"1114:2F74C2:C614CB:E6400D:69FE8548"},"id":"5628b2a7-aa73-4740-8f4a-7bc67d19a77f","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:52:39.584Z","parentId":"d3a2296c-86c9-4ce5-a480-ed118c944589"}
